### Build-a-Bank · Step 6 · Seeing Spring Boot auto-configuration via Actuator
### Start hello-service first:  make run-hello   (or  .\mvnw.cmd -pl services/hello spring-boot:run )

@host = http://localhost:8080

### The auto-configuration REPORT: which auto-configs matched (positiveMatches) and which were
### skipped and WHY (negativeMatches). This is how Boot's "magic" becomes visible.
GET {{host}}/actuator/conditions
# curl: curl -s http://localhost:8080/actuator/conditions | jq '.contexts."hello-service".positiveMatches | keys | length'

### Every bound @ConfigurationProperties object (sensitive values are sanitized)
GET {{host}}/actuator/configprops

### Every bean in the container
GET {{host}}/actuator/beans

### The resolved environment (property sources, in precedence order; secrets sanitized)
GET {{host}}/actuator/env

### Request mappings (every URL → handler)
GET {{host}}/actuator/mappings
